content.description: Small, yes.  Potentially a new age classic?  For sure.  Start on the prominent flat ledge on the left side, probably pull up and far right to a pinch and finish it up.  A pure and high quality little problem.  Also easily accessible and not so hard to find.
content.location: 100 feet off the trail and ten minutes from the car probably.  Walk up the East Bluff Trail. Pass Elephant Rock and the cave.., go up steps and along the loose cliff next to the trail. Just after the cliff go up more steps and in a couple hundred feet the boulder is 100 feet off to the right in the trees. Mutual Attraction faces the trail. This is between the EB north talus and the Monolith Talus.

content.description: Home to a singular quality line, Mutual Attraction and a few easier things as well... So far.
